         <cell width="340">
            <color r="255" g="248" b="178">To unlock the rockhopper penguin in challenge or campaign games, you must earn a 2-star zoo fame rating for your zoo.</color>
            <p/>Rockhopper penguins earned their name by hopping among boulders on the rocky islands they inhabit. They are a sub-Antarctic species of penguin, so they are found primarily on southern islands such as the Falklands, Macquarie Island, and the Antipodes.
            <p/>Sporting a handsome, distinctive crest and blood-red eyes, rockhoppers are as aggressive as their intense stare suggests. It is common for them to fight over premium nesting sites on the rocky terrain they inhabit. Small and powerful, their webbed feet and flippers make them formidable swimmers and hunters.
				<p/>Rockhoppers prey on lantern fish, krill, and sometimes small squid. They are themselves prey to blue sharks, leopard seals, and fur seals, and their eggs and chicks are often vulnerable on land to gulls and other birds.
				<p/>Because they make their nests on rocky shorelines, their ability to hop out of the water and up onto the rocks is an important survival skill.  
